title: For Sale:  AR in .300 AAC Blackout, Odinworks SS Barrel, Spikes Tactical lower, Magpul hardware
postcontent:
Spike’s Tactical AR in .300 AAC Blackout, $900 obo

For sale only, no trades
Local sales only
Cash only
I will not ship

For sale, AR chambered in .300 AAC Blackout . Features a Spikes Tactical Spartan lower, Odinworks stainless barrel, Odinworks forend, and assorted Magpul hardware. This is an accurate shooting rifle that uses the increasingly popular .300 Blackout cartridge. It’s pretty amazing to fire a 30 caliber projectile downrange using all the same parts as a .223 rifle, with only the barrel being different.  The .300 AAC was designed to give the ballistic performance of the 7.62x39 in an AR platform without requiring a full redesign. The result is an incredible success, especially when you consider the .300 BO generates 16.7 per cent more energy at 300 meters than the 7.62×39 or the AK round. The .300 BO is a very accurate cartridge, and coupled with the Odinworks barrel it is a great shooting combo. 

My first day firing this rifle, I picked up a couple boxes of Remington .300 BO with 120 grain supersonic hollowpoints at Academy Sports and hit the range in Unioi. It was not perfect conditions by any stretch. It was very windy, and the backstop netting kept blowing around (along with my target). Timing it between gusts as best I could, I still managed a 3.5” group of 10 shots at 50 yards, with the included iron peep sight. I don’t doubt that I could shrink this considerably if I had a proper rest. Throw in a scope, and it would drive tacks. See target picture (last one in the pictures list).  

Condition is very good. There are some scratches from general use on the forend. Internals are just barely getting broken in. Please see larger pictures in the links below.

AR with Spikes Tactical “Spartan” lower

title: For Sale:  SCAM WARNING: BEWARE/PLEASE READ/cannot mail firearms
postcontent:
Folks, I've met some really decent people on here and this is a good site. 
However, the Scam artists never quit. And we've got a few on the local site right now.

Do NOT trust any ad that mentions 'mailing a firearm to you'. It's a fraud. They will answer the phone and really try to get your trust, AND YOUR MONEY. 

You CANNOT mail firearms to an individual. It's a scam. 
A firearm can only be mailed to an FFL (Federal Firearms License holder). 
Any ad promising to mail you a firearm otherwise, is a scam.
The only way to legally mail a firearm (and it is done quite often) is to have the firearm mailed to an FFL, who will receive it for you. You have to send a copy of the FFL to the seller beforehand. NEVER send money to an unverified seller.  

I realize this is elementary to a lot of us, but we need to stick together and protect each other and the new guy, too. 

Thank you. 
God Bless the 2nd Amendment.

title: For Sale:   Taurus PT92AF (Beretta 92F) 9mm Semiautomatic Pistol
postcontent:
This is an early 1980’s production Taurus PT92AF full-size semiautomatic pistol originally intended for police and military use.
History: The PT92 is seen by many as a ‘clone’ of the highly regarded Beretta Model 92F, but when Taurus made the first PT-92 in 1980, they didn’t copy or reverse-engineer the Beretta Model 92F as is sometimes believed. Instead, they bought Beretta’s entire Brazilian factory with its machinery, parts and plans and even kept Beretta’s trained workers at their stations. The early Taurus PT92 are, in some aspects, actually preferred by many enthusiasts over the considerably more expensive Beretta due to improvements made when Taurus took over production.( specifically replacing plastic parts with stainless steel )
Testimonial: Chris Dumm writing for thetruthaboutguns.com after
an extensive side by side comparison of the Taurus PT92 and the Beretta Model 92F had this opinion:
“A damned fine pistol and a great value. After comparing and shooting the Taurus and Beretta side-by-side, I would choose the Taurus first”…………
